  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - DRUID</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>SNOW DERVISHES</font> - <small>Taxyll, Povar</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>When you hit lvl 34 and get your Iceclad Ring spell, use it and port yourself there.<br>
<br>
Make sure you have mana and sow up.  In fact I buff for battle and med up before I port there.  Reason is because the very thing you are looking for likes to attack uninvis'd unsuspecting first time visitors at the port site, and that frequently is a traveler's welcome and initiation to the world of Velious.<br>
<br>
Nonetheless your victim may help you find him soon as you arrive. Dont stop here however because quadkiting is the game.  Ensnare up to 4 of these guys,snow dervs that is.  I do mean use ensnare since it lasts longer than snare and because you may have to track to round up 4,and will spend more time grouping them.  I have found that in the process of maneuvering them together you can get some brief med time in as they catch up with you and group together( the "brief med while grouping the quad" thing is easier at lvl 35 since you can just sit to med and watch as they get closer). <br>
<br>
I have found that i can usually get to FM, recovering the ensnare mana before actually starting to nuke them with Lightning strike.<br>
<br>
I recommend that you pull your quad away from the druid ring and towards the ocean ledge to avoid running into giants, wolves or other dervs. I usually kite up and down the ledge facing directly out from the ring entrance.<br>
<br>
The only loot i have gotten off the dervs is a chill dagger, but a full blue bub of exp with each quad kill.(That is til lvl 40)You must loot quickly to because their corpses decay very quickly.<br>
<br>
I also recommend keeping lev on, because if you run out of mana you can frequently run across the water to an adjacent island out of there aggro range and med up.<br>
<br>
This area (around the druid ring) is rarely busy.  Not to many snow derv groups out there, so you will have free reign and all the dervs you want to kill.<br>
<br>
This is a great option(better beginning at lvl 35) if you are waiting to group because your prey is right next to the port site. If you die you are essentially bound there with the Iceclad port.(Easier to convince a exp rezzing cleric to tag along for cr since corpse will be close)<br>
<br>
You may find that you are the hero of the day since you tend to control the derv crowd for the arriving travelers.<br>
<br>
If they resist lightning strike unevenly and separate, they usually regen quick enough to aggro again and can be regrouped to finish them off with Lightning strike, or if you have enough mana just dd 3 to death and finish the 4th off(when he no longer aggroes on you) with melee to work on the melee skill of the day.<br>
<br>
Whatever you do don't go Ld while quad kiting these guys cause they hit hard and you will log on to a naked corpse.<br>
<br>
Everything close to the ring aggroes you so look carefully around as you kite.  Easy to run into others if you dont pay attention. <br>
<br>
Dervs start to go green at lvl 40, but there are still plenty of blues.
<br>

</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
